# 📏 File Size Limit

**This is a CURSOR-SPECIFIC rule file.**

**Full documentation:** [docs/standards/rules/file-size-limit.md](../../docs/standards/rules/file-size-limit.md)

## Rule for Cursor

Cursor MUST enforce file size limits:

- **WARN** at 200 lines
- **ERROR** at 250 lines
- **SUGGEST** extraction to components

## Quick Reference

```typescript
// ❌ BEFORE - 300 lines
export default function DashboardPage() {
  // ... 300 lines
}

// ✅ AFTER - Extracted
export default function DashboardPage() {
  return (
    <div>
      <DashboardHeader />
      <StatsCards />
      <RecentActivity />
    </div>
  )
}
```

## AI Agent Instructions

When file > 200 lines:
1. WARN user about file size
2. IDENTIFY extractable components
3. SUGGEST specific extractions
4. NEVER add more code to large files

---

